From: Cole Leavitt <cole@unwrap.rs>
Subject: bindgen: fix type declaration resolution for clang/libclang >= 22

Backport of rust-lang/rust-bindgen PR #3278 to bindgen 0.69.4 (bundled
in Firefox ESR 140). LLVM PR #147835 changed TagType::getDecl() to
return the syntactically-encountered declaration instead of always
resolving to the definition. This breaks bindgen's transitive type
discovery for typedef'd enums used as struct field types.

The fix: after clang_getTypeDeclaration(), follow forward declarations
to their definitions via clang_getCursorDefinition(). This is a no-op
on older clang (getDecl already returned the definition) and restores
correct behavior on clang >= 22.

--- a/third_party/rust/bindgen/clang.rs
+++ b/third_party/rust/bindgen/clang.rs
@@ -1211,11 +1211,10 @@
 
     /// Get a cursor pointing to this type's declaration.
     pub(crate) fn declaration(&self) -> Cursor {
-        unsafe {
-            Cursor {
-                x: clang_getTypeDeclaration(self.x),
-            }
-        }
+        let decl = Cursor {
+            x: unsafe { clang_getTypeDeclaration(self.x) },
+        };
+        decl.definition().unwrap_or(decl)
     }
 
     /// Get the canonical declaration of this type, if it is available.
